headline: Palantir Is Best S&P 500 Stock in November. This Chemical Materials Company Is the Worst.
summary: With the holiday season quickly approaching, a software company has found itself top of the good list in November.  Palantir Technologies  has been the best performer in the  this month, while chemical materials company  Celanese  has fared the worst through Wednesday’s close of trading, according to Dow Jones Market Data.  Palantir  has gained 49% this month, putting the stock on track for its best monthly performance since February.
